<p>NOTE: Earnings per share before one time charge grew 67 pct from the March 1996 quarter to $0.30 per share.</p>
<p>A one time charge of $10 million was incurred from the sale of Symantec's Networking business to Hewlett-Packard.</p>
<p>For the full year, net income before acquisition, restructuring and other expenses was $43.4 million, or $.78 per share.</p>
<p>Net income after acquisition, restructuring and other expenses was $26.0 million or $.47 per share compared to a prior year loss of $39.8 million or a loss of $.76 per share.</p>
<p>Acquisition, restructuring and other expenses in the current year were primarily related to the sale of Norton Administrator for Networks and restructuring charges. Prior year charges were primarily related to the acquisition of Delrina Corporation.</p>
